# load library
library(tidyverse)
library(ggthemes)
library(scales)
library(ggrastr)
library(vegan)

tidy_col <- c("#18BC9C","#CCBE93","#a6cee3","#1f78b4","#b2df8a","#fb9a99","#fdbf6f","#ff7f00","#cab2d6","#6a3d9a")

dbRDA

## Japanese 4D cohort
files <- list.files("data/JP_4D_RDA/", pattern = "results.tsv") %>% paste0("data/JP_4D_RDA/", .)
keep <- files %>% str_detect("dbRDA")
files <- files[keep]

df <- c()
for(i in files){
  data <- i %>% str_remove(".tsv.dbRDA.*") %>% str_remove(".*\\.")
  d <- read.delim(i)
  d %>% head()
  
  temp <- data.frame(data = data, r2 = d$R2.adj[nrow(d)])
  df <- rbind(df, temp)
}

df$data <- df$data %>% str_to_sentence() %>% str_replace("Bss", "BSS") %>% str_replace("\\_", " ")
df$data <- df$data %>% str_replace("All count", "All metadata")
df$cohort <- "Japanese 4D"
df.jp <- df %>% filter(data != "All metadata")
df.jp <- df.jp %>% arrange(-r2)
df.jp$data <- df.jp$data %>% factor(levels = df.jp$data)

p.jp <- ggplot(df.jp, aes(x = reorder(data, -r2, sum), y = r2, fill = data)) +
  theme_mine() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent) +
  ggtitle("Japanese 4D") +
  ylab("Explained variance") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5)) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = tidy_col) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", alpha = 0.6)
p.jp

world <- map_data("world")
md.global <- read_rds("data/metalog/md.rds")

pseud <- 1E-4
model <- read_rds("out/model/model_metacardis.motus25.rds")
model <- model[[1]]
d.global <- read_rds("data/metalog/d.rds")
d.global$`Shannon diversity` <- diversity(d.global)
md.global$count <- predict(model, scale(log10(d.global + pseud)))

model.sp <- model$trainingData %>% colnames()

d.global2 <- d.global[, -ncol(d.global)]
keep <- colnames(d.global2) %in% model.sp
model.sp.rel <- apply(d.global2[, !keep], 1, sum)
md.global$model_sp <- model.sp.rel
md.global$diversity <- d.global$`Shannon diversity`

## exclude disease patients
md.global <- md.global %>% filter(disease == "Control")

## exclude individuals treated with antibiotics
md.global$antibiotic <- md.global$antibiotic %>% str_replace("no", "") %>% str_replace("No", "")
md.global$intervention <- md.global$intervention %>% str_replace("ABX.*", "ABX")

md.global <- md.global %>% 
  mutate(antibiotics_binary = case_when(
    intervention == "ABX" ~ 1,    
    antibiotic != "" ~ 1,
    TRUE ~ 0
  ))
md.global <- md.global %>% filter(antibiotics_binary == 0)


md <- md.global %>% select(geographic_location, count) %>% group_by(geographic_location) %>% summarise(m = mean(count), n = n())
colnames(md) <- c("region", "ml", "n")
md <- md %>% filter(n > 20)

# Get world map data
world_map <- map_data("world")
worldSubset <- inner_join(world, md, by = "region")

keep <- !world$region %in% worldSubset$region
world.add <- world[keep, ]
world.add$ml <- 0
world.add$n <- 0

worldSubset <- rbind(worldSubset, world.add)

## world bank 4 categories
who <- read.delim("data/world_bank_classifications.txt", header = T)
who$country <- who$country %>% str_replace("United States", "USA")
md.global$geographic_location[md.global$geographic_location == ""] <- NA

for(i in 1:nrow(md.global)){
  keep <- who$country %in% md.global$geographic_location[i]
  if(sum(keep) == 0){
    md.global$developed[i] <- NA
  }else{
    md.global$developed[i] <- who$category[keep]
  }
}

md.global$developed <- md.global$developed %>% factor(levels = c("High income", "Upper-middle income", "Lower-middle income", "Low income"))
pair <- combn(levels(md.global$developed), 2, simplify=F)
md.global2 <- md.global %>% filter(disease == "Control") %>% filter(antibiotics_binary == 0)

library(scales)
p1 <- md.global2 %>% filter(geographic_location != "NA") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = developed, y = model_sp, fill = developed)) +
  theme_mine() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),  plot.margin=unit(c(0.5,0.5,0.5,1), "lines")) +
  ylab("Fraction of uncommon species") +
  geom_violin(aes(fill = developed), col = NA, alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.size = -1, width = 0.2, fill = "white") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = tidy_col) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent) +
  ggpubr::stat_compare_means(comparisons = pair, tip.length = 0, method = "wilcox.test", size = 2, label = "p.signif") +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank(), legend.position = "none") +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 1, vjust = 1))

md.global3 <- md.global2 %>% filter(model_sp != 0)
model1 <- glm(md.global3$count ~ md.global3$developed)
model2 <- glm(md.global3$count ~ md.global3$developed + log10(md.global3$model_sp))
model1.ci <- model1 %>% confint()
## Waiting for profiling to be done...
model2.ci <- model2 %>% confint()
## Waiting for profiling to be done...
model1.df <- summary(model1)$coefficients[-1, ] %>% data.frame() %>% rownames_to_column() %>% mutate(model = "model1")
model2.df <- summary(model2)$coefficients[-1, ] %>% data.frame() %>% rownames_to_column() %>% mutate(model = "model2")

model1.df$Std..Error <- model1.ci[-1, 2] - model1.df$Std..Error
model2.df$Std..Error <- model2.ci[-1, 2] - model1.df$Std..Error

df <- rbind(model1.df, model2.df[-nrow(model2.df), ])
colnames(df) <- c("name", "e", "error", "t", "p", "model")
df$name <- df$name %>% str_replace(".*developed", "")

df$name <- factor(df$name, levels = c("Upper-middle income", "Lower-middle income", "Low income"))
p2 <- ggplot(df, aes(x = name, y = e, col = model)) +
  theme_mine() +

Adjustment for microbial load

df <- read_rds("out/rds/df.global_jaapanese.rds")
temp1 <- lm(df$shannon ~ df$age + df$study)
temp2 <- lm(df$shannon ~ df$age + df$count + df$study)
temp3 <- lm(df$shannon ~ df$sex + df$study)
temp4 <- lm(df$shannon ~ df$sex + df$count + df$study)

temp1.ci <- temp1 %>% confint()
temp2.ci <- temp2 %>% confint()
temp3.ci <- temp3 %>% confint()
temp4.ci <- temp4 %>% confint()

temp1 <- summary(temp1)$coefficients[2, ] %>% t() %>% data.frame() %>% mutate(a = "Age", b = "Before adjustment")
temp2 <- summary(temp2)$coefficients[2, ] %>% t() %>% data.frame() %>% mutate(a = "Age", b = "After adjustment")
temp3 <- summary(temp3)$coefficients[2, ] %>% t() %>% data.frame() %>% mutate(a = "Sex (male)", b = "Before adjustment")
temp4 <- summary(temp4)$coefficients[2, ] %>% t() %>% data.frame() %>% mutate(a = "Sex (male)", b = "After adjustment")

df.forest <- rbind(temp1, temp2, temp3, temp4) %>% data.frame()
colnames(df.forest) <- c("e", "error", "t", "p", "factor", "adj")

df.forest$ci.high <- c(temp1.ci[2, 2], temp2.ci[2, 2], temp3.ci[2, 2], temp4.ci[2, 2])
df.forest$ci.low <- c(temp1.ci[2, 1], temp2.ci[2, 1], temp3.ci[2, 1], temp4.ci[2, 1])
df.forest$adj <- df.forest$adj %>% factor(levels = c("Before adjustment", "After adjustment"))

p.forest <- ggplot(df.forest, aes(x = adj, y = e)) +
  theme_mine() +
  geom_point() +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymax = ci.high, ymin = ci.low), width = 0) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = 2, col = "tomato") +
  ylab("Effect size\non Shannon diversity") +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 1)) +
  facet_wrap(~factor, scales = "free")
